Actually, this would work for me, yes.  Just means searching and replacing
for each type of field header (maybe I should learn more about MSWord
macros...).  Would a similar solution also work for making sure the data is
search engine ready?  I was figuring the "+" would not only help me, but
would get around worrying about how different peoples' lines are broken when
it comes time to have some software parse the datafile for searching purposes.

The advantage of using a visible character for line endings is:  People can
simply take the whole Web page for a year off the Web by copying it.  And
then drop that text file into their local search engine (which will be set
up to ignore all line breaks and only respond to "+" as the end of a field).
But maybe the search engine will simply recognize all the field headers?

I'm not sure about these matters, but guess we can hold off on insisting on
adding anything to the setlists for a while :-)

- --Nathan


